  "prompt": "What are Top 10 worst black Friday disasters?",
  "response": "Black Friday is notorious for instances of chaos and sometimes tragedy, and several events have stood out over the years due to their severity. Here are some of the worst Black Friday disasters:\n\n1. **2008 Walmart Stampede**: A temporary employee named Jdimytai Damour was killed in a stampede at a Walmart in Valley Stream, New York, when shoppers broke down the doors and stormed into the store.\n\n2. **2006 Southern California Shooting**: A dispute over a PlayStation 3 at a parking lot in Southern California escalated, resulting in a shooting where a man was critically injured.\n\n3. **2011 Target Pepper Spray Incident**: At a Target in Los Angeles, a woman used pepper spray on fellow shoppers to gain an advantage in grabbing discounted items, causing injuries to roughly 20 people.\n\n4. **2013 Kmart Shooting**: In Chicago, a dispute in the parking lot of a Kmart ended in a shooting, leading to the death of a 21-year-old man.\n\n5. **2016 San Antonio Shooting**: At a Walmart in San Antonio, Texas, shots were fired outside the store, leaving a man dead and two others injured.\n\n6. **2018 Alabama Mall Shooting**: Hoover, Alabama, saw a police officer fatally shooting a suspected gunman at the Riverchase Galleria mall during a fight that led to panic among shoppers.\n\n7. **2010 Wisconsin Scenario**: At a Madison, Wisconsin, Toys 'R' Us, shoppers trampled over one another as the doors opened, resulting in injuries and significant property damage.\n\n8. **2008 Toys 'R' Us Shooting**: In Palm Desert, California, a confrontation inside a Toys 'R' Us escalated into a shootout, resulting in two deaths.\n\n9. **2012 South Philadelphia Walmart Brawl**: An argument over cutting in line at a Walmart in South Philadelphia led to a physical altercation involving several shoppers and requiring police intervention.\n\n10. **2013 Virginia Walmart Incident**: At a Walmart in Virginia, a man pulled a gun on another shopper during a dispute over a parking space, leading to a dangerous situation that required police to mitigate.\n\nThese events highlight the extreme circumstances that can occur amid the frenzy of Black Friday shopping, underscoring the need for effective crowd management and security measures.",
